// ============================================================================
// CRITICAL NOTES FOR IMPLEMENTATION
// ============================================================================

/*
PRIORITY IMPLEMENTATION NOTES:

1. MAITAKE GPS MARKING STRATEGY:
   - Implement feature to mark productive oak trees
   - Track annual return rates (same trees produce for years)
   - Priority notification system for known producers

2. BLACK TRUMPET CAMOUFLAGE ALERT:
   - UI warning about visibility challenges
   - Search pattern recommendations
   - Moss habitat flagging in county data

3. LOBSTER MUSHROOM SAFETY VALIDATION:
   - Interior color check reminder
   - Half-parasitized rejection criteria
   - Firmness assessment guide

4. MILK CAP LATEX TASTE TEST:
   - MANDATORY safety protocol in UI
   - Step-by-step testing instructions
   - Reject criteria for acrid/peppery latex

5. TRUMPET CHANTERELLE SUBSPECIES:
   - Separate probability calculations for tubaeformis (conifer bogs)
   - Elevation-based subspecies recommendations
   - Wetland/bog habitat flagging

CONFIDENCE LEVELS BY SPECIES:
- Maitake: HIGH (oak association well-documented)
- Milk Caps: HIGH (oak association, safety protocols clear)
- Black Trumpets: MEDIUM-HIGH (safe but habitat less quantified)
- Trumpet Chanterelles: MEDIUM (less documented than golden chanterelles)
- Lobster: MEDIUM-HIGH (safe but parasitic ecology complex)

DATA GAPS REQUIRING FIELD VALIDATION:
- Precise NH elevation-based timing for all species
- Soil temperature thresholds (most data from cultivation or related species)
- Post-rain fruiting windows (mostly anecdotal)
- County-specific microhabitat preferences
*/
